article.description: Lyndra Littles scored 14 of her 23 points in the final seven minutes to help Virginia (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) hold off Georgia 62-60 on Friday night.
article.headline: No. 15 Virginia finishes strong to avoid upset
article.linkText: No. 15 Virginia comes back to hold off Georgia
article.story:
CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. -- Lyndra Littles scored 14 of her 23 points in the final seven minutes to help Virginia (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) hold off Georgia 62-60 on Friday night.

Georgia led 58-57 with just over one minute remaining, but Littles' three-point play with 50 seconds left and Enong Stovall's two free throws 30 seconds later made up a 5-2 Virginia run in the final minute to seal the win.

Monica Wright led the Cavaliers (12-2) with 24 points.

Ashley Houts led the Lady Bulldogs (9-5) with 19 points and Porsha Phillips chipped in with 10. Angel Robinson grabbed 11 rebounds.

Georgia outshot Virginia in both halves, finishing with a 40.6 percent mark from the field (23 of 57) compared to just 35.5 percent (20 of 56) for the Cavaliers.

Virginia won the rebounding battle 38-35, though, and got 25 points from its bench versus 11 for Georgia.
